# FitClub UI — Design token rules

All new UI **must** follow these rules. No exceptions.

## Colors

- **Backgrounds**: Use `bg-neutral-50` or `bg-background` (Tailwind). In React Native: `backgroundColor: theme.colors.background` or `theme.colors.surface` from `useTheme()`.
- **Text**: Use `text-neutral-900` or `text-primary-500` (Tailwind). In RN: `color: theme.colors.text`, `theme.colors.textSecondary`, or `theme.colors.primary`.
- **Never** use raw hex values (`#...`), `rgb()`, `rgba()`, or named colors (`'white'`, `'black'`) in components. Only the design-system token file may define hex; components use theme tokens only.

## Spacing

- Use the **spacing scale only**. No arbitrary padding or margin (e.g. no `p-[13px]`, `margin: 17`, `padding: 20`).
- Tailwind: `p-2`, `p-4`, `m-4`, `gap-2`, etc. from the theme scale (4, 8, 16, 24, 32…).
- React Native: `theme.spacing.xs`, `theme.spacing.sm`, `theme.spacing.md`, `theme.spacing.lg`, `theme.spacing.xl` (and `xxs`, `xxl`, `xxxl` where defined). No magic numbers.

## Border radius

- Use **border radius tokens only** (e.g. `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg` in Tailwind; `theme.radius.sm`, `theme.radius.md`, `theme.radius.lg` in RN). No arbitrary values like `borderRadius: 7`.

## No inline styles

- **Tailwind**: Prefer utility classes; avoid `style={{ ... }}` with raw values.
- **React Native**: Prefer `StyleSheet.create` and theme-driven styles. When you need theme values, use a single dynamic object keyed by theme (e.g. `style={[styles.card, { backgroundColor: theme.colors.surface, padding: theme.spacing.md }]}`) — do not build ad-hoc style objects with hard-coded numbers or colors. Never put hex or magic numbers in inline style objects.

## Summary

| Do | Don't |
|----|--------|
| `bg-background`, `theme.colors.background` | `#ffffff`, `backgroundColor: '#fff'` |
| `text-neutral-900`, `theme.colors.text` | `color: '#111'`, `'black'` |
| `p-4`, `theme.spacing.md` | `padding: 20`, `p-[17px]` |
| `rounded-lg`, `theme.radius.lg` | `borderRadius: 12`, `rounded-[7px]` |
| StyleSheet + theme / Tailwind classes | Inline style objects with raw hex or arbitrary numbers |
